$$\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}.$$
Similarly, we calculate the cross product of $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{b}$:
$$\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \times \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} -1 \\ 1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}.$$

Now, let $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \\ v_3 \end{pmatrix}.$ We want to satisfy the equations:
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{v} \times \mathbf{a} &= \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a} \\
\mathbf{v} \times \mathbf{b} &= \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}
\end{align*}
This gives us two systems of equations:
